# Example hostname pool. On first run the dispenser copies this to
# /var/lib/svk/hostname-pool (on the data volume) if that file doesn't exist;
# edit the REAL pool there, not this example — the example is baked into the
# image and reset on every update.
#
# One hostname label per line. '#' comments and blank lines are ignored. Labels
# must be valid DNS labels (lowercase letters, digits, hyphens) so they resolve
# cleanly under Tailscale MagicDNS. Give yourself more names than machines.

